Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

Wash and dry produce. Cut @broccoli crowns{1%pound} into bite-size pieces.

Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack until lightly browned and crisp, ~{15-20%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

In the last ~{1-2%minutes} of cooking, sprinkle broccoli with @Sargento® 4 Cheese Mexican Shredded{8%ounce} and continue roasting until cheese has melted.

> Recipe Suggestion: In step 3, toss broccoli with oil, salt, pepper, and Southwest Spice.